&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Vast, our mission is to contribute to a future where billions of people are living and thriving in space. Vast is developing next-generation space stations to ensure a continuous human presence in space for America and its allies, enabling advanced microgravity research and manufacturing, and unlocking a new space economy for government, corporate, and private customers. Using an incremental, hardware-rich and low-cost approach, Vast is rapidly developing its multi-module Haven Station. Haven Demo’s 2025 success made Vast the only operational commercial space station company to fly and operate its own spacecraft. Next, Haven-1 is expected to become the world’s first commercial space station when it launches, followed by additional Haven modules to enable permanent human presence by 2030. Our team is all-in, committed to executing our mission safely and on time. If you want to work with the most talented people on Earth furthering space exploration for humanity, come join us.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vast is looking for an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Events Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, reporting to the&lt;strong&gt; Senior Manager of Experience, &lt;/strong&gt;to support the development of the systems that will be required for the design and build of human-rated space stations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will support events from concept development to on-the-ground execution.&amp;nbsp;You’ll support the execution of events both internal and external for Vast. These include domestic and international industry conferences, business development events, and VIP experiences. You’ll help ensure every event is thoughtfully executed, on brand, and delivered with excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
